ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.299                Enzyme
NAME        protein N-terminal monomethyltransferase;
            NRMT2 (gene name);
            METTL11B (gene name);
            N-terminal monomethylase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:N-terminal-(A,P,S)PK-[protein] monomethyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + N-terminal-(A,P,S)PK-[protein] = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N-terminal-N-methyl-N-(A,P,S)PK-[protein]
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            N-terminal-(A,P,S)PK-[protein]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            N-terminal-N-methyl-N-(A,P,S)PK-[protein]
COMMENT     This enzyme methylates the N-terminus of target proteins containing the N-terminal motif [Ala/Pro/Ser]-Pro-Lys after the initiator L-methionine is cleaved. In contrast to EC 2.1.1.244, protein N-terminal methyltransferase, the protein only adds one methyl group to the N-terminal.
